revision.text:
{{Unreferenced stub|date=December 2009}}
'''Alternative frequency''' (or '''AF''') is an option that allows a receiver to re-tune to a different [[frequency]] that provides the same station, when the first [[Signaling (telecommunication)|signal]] becomes too weak (e.g. when moving out of range). This is often used in car [[Receiver (home stereo)|stereo system]]s, enabled by [[Radio Data System]] (RDS), or the [[United States|U.S.]]-based [[Radio Broadcast Data System]] ([[RBDS]]).

