{{Infobox language |name=Alu |altname= |pronunciation= |states=[[China]] and [[Laos]] |region=[[Yunnan]] |ethnicity= |speakers= |date= |ref= |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=(unclassified) |fam6= |fam7= |iso3=none |glotto= |glottorefname= }}
'''Alu''' (Chinese: 阿鲁) is an unclassified [[Loloish language]] of [[Yunnan]], [[China]]. It is spoken in [[Jinping Miao, Yao, and Dai Autonomous County]], [[Lüchun County]], [[Jiangcheng Hani and Yi Autonomous County]], and [[Yuanyang County, Yunnan]]. The Alu are also referred to by other ethnic groups as Luwu 鲁乌 or Luowu 倮乌.<ref name="wanmin">{{cite web|url=http://www.wanmin.org/minzu/alu|title=阿鲁民族 - 万民网|website=wanmin.org|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> There are also 500 to 600 Alu people in two villages of Ou Tay District, Phongsali province.<ref name>Schliesinger, Joachim. 2003. Ethnic Groups of Laos. Vol. 4: Sino-Tibetan-Speaking Peoples. Bangkok: White Lotus Press.</ref>
The Alu also have a [[mouth organ]] with five pipes that they play during the "Abei festival 阿卑节" ("maiden festival").<ref name="yixueyanjiu">{{cite web|url=http://www.yixueyanjiu.com/news/13/z_13_24201.html|website=yixueyanjiu.com|title=红河金平"姑娘节" 彝族阿鲁人的情人节_彝学研究网|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref>
==Classification== Hsiu (2017)<ref>Hsiu, Andrew. 2017. ''[https://www.academia.edu/35542553/The_Lawu_languages_footprints_along_the_Red_River_valley_corridor The Lawu languages: footprints along the Red River valley corridor]''.</ref> suggests that Awu may be related to [[Lalo language|Lalo]], but that this is uncertain due to the lack of data.
==Distribution== In [[Jinping Miao, Yao, and Dai Autonomous County|Jinping County]], Alu is spoken in Yakouzhe Village 丫口遮村, Laojizhai Township 老集寨乡 (in the villages of Luopan 罗盘,<ref name="ynszxc">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189103|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县老集寨乡丫口遮村委会罗盘上寨村|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref><ref name="ynszxc2">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189104|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县老集寨乡丫口遮村委会罗盘下寨村|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Tiantou 田头,<ref name="ynszxc3">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189105|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县老集寨乡丫口遮村委会田头村|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Huilongzhai 回龙寨,<ref name="ynszxc4">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189102|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县老集寨乡丫口遮村委会回龙寨村|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Laozhai 老寨,<ref name="ynszxc5">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189106|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县老集寨乡丫口遮村委会老寨村|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Zhongzhai 中寨,<ref name="ynszxc6">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189109|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县老集寨乡丫口遮村委会中寨村|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Xihadi 西哈底,<ref name="ynszxc7">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189110|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县老集寨乡丫口遮村委会西哈底村|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Heishan 黑山,<ref name="ynszxc8">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189111|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县老集寨乡丫口遮村委会黑山村|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Amilong 阿咪笼,<ref name="ynszxc9">{{cite web|url=http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189108|website=ynszxc.gov.cn|title=金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县老集寨乡丫口遮村委会阿咪聋村|accessdate=2017-12-30}}</ref> Kabianzhai 卡边寨,<ref name="ynszxc10">{{cite web|u